==English==

===Alternative spellings===
*'''koeksijster'''
*'''koeksuster'''
*'''koesister'''

===Etymology===
{{D.}}, from ''[[koek]]'', cake + ''[[sissen]]'', to sizzle

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# (''South Africa'') A traditional [[Malay]] [[confection]] consisting of a [[deep-fried]] [[twisted]] or [[plaited]] [[doughnut]] dipped in [[syrup]] immediately after cooking.

====Quotations====
*'''2003''' Orania is unveiling a statue to the '''koeksister''', that syrupy delicacy so loved by Afrikaners. When I tell people, everyone thinks it must be a joke. &mdash; Sunday Times<!--which Sunday Times?-->

===References===
*''A Dictionary of South African English'', Jean Bradford, Oxford, 1978

